-- India’s NMDC Appoints Nanda to Succeed Som as Company Chairman
-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 2012-01-01T03:49:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-01/india-s-nmdc-appoints-nanda-to-succeed-som-as-company-chairman.html
NMDC Ltd. (NMDC) ,  India ’s largest iron ore
producer, said it appointed Narendra Kumar Nanda to succeed Rana Som as chairman and managing director.  Som retired on Dec. 31, NMDC said in an e-mailed statement
yesterday. Nanda will retain his position as technical director,
the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Tighe at 
 ptighe@bloomberg.net . 